3A4 inhibitor, a progressive dosage reduction may be required over a longer period if the corticosteroid is to be withdrawn from therapy, as there may be a significant risk of adrenal suppression.', 'Metabolism', 'The possibility of increased corticosteroid effects should be considered during coadministration with potent and moderate CYP450 3A4 inhibitors.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/95536/', '', 'Dirithromycin, Lincomycin, Azithromycin, Clindamycin, Minocycline, Clindamycin, Vitamin A, Isotretinoin, Dexamethasone, Chloramphenicol, Fluorometholone, More', 'Fluocinolone acetonide, Fluocinolone acetonide, Fluorometholone', 1767369485);
